'We're pleased we have a replay to play,' the Everton boss is quoted as saying on the FA website. 'Draws are an emotionally tricky result in terms of how you feel about them.'

'It's still only a draw but when you are the team that gets the equaliser late in the game, it can feel like a victory. In the same way, when you concede late on, it can feel like a defeat.'

Martinez, who led Everton to a credible draw against Premier League champions Manchester City on Saturday, is expecting an open game against Sam Allardyce's high-flying West Ham.

